OL,4,G1855FFour in a Bed
OL,5,     GThere once was a flight attendant
OL,6,     Gcalled Meg, who decided to run a
OL,7,     GB&B instead. When her guests came
OL,8,     Gto stay, at her place - Lamlash
OL,9,     GBay, did she put the competition
OL,10,     Gto bed? _WorldPoetryDay
OL,11,G1925FFour in a Bed
OL,12,     GPayment day's time to settle some
OL,13,     Gscores, and see what's gone on
OL,14,     Gbehind closed doors. After a
OL,15,     Glavatory let-down and a breakfast
OL,16,     Gsin, whose B&B will take the win?
OL,17,     G_WorldPoetryDay
OL,18,G2000F24 Hours in A&E
OL,19,     GHurt knee, high heart rate;
OL,20,     Gmotorcycle accident; 'Your
OL,21,     Gfamily's here.' _worldpoetryday
